 Police on Friday gunned down a man suspected have shot and killed a police officer. The DCI said they received a tip-off and trailed him to his hideout in Githurai Kimbo. "Detectives working on a tip-off, yesterday trailed an armed gangster who had killed a police officer and escaped with his pistol," the DCI tweeted. A pistol with nine bullets was recovered during the raid. "He was put to sleep at his hideout in Githurai Kimbo when he defied an order to surrender," the DCI said. Click here for the latest political news